A tree with hanging vines is an unused scenery object. It has an appearance similar to the ropeswing in Brimhaven, but with two hanging vines instead of a single rope. This bears a very strong resemblance to the ropeswing's original appearance in RuneScape Classic.

The tree may have been intended as the original model of the ropeswing or as a different agility shortcut. The tree has no interaction options, which could instead indicate that the tree was intended to just be decorative scenery in a jungle region.

A '''tree''' with hanging vines is an unused scenery object. It has an appearance similar to the [[Ropeswing (Brimhaven)|ropeswing]] in [[Brimhaven]], but with two hanging vines instead of a single rope. This bears a very strong resemblance to the ropeswing's [[classicrsw:Tree Swing|original appearance]] in RuneScape Classic.

The tree may have been intended as the original model of the ropeswing or as a different agility shortcut. The tree has no interaction options, which could instead indicate that the tree was intended to just be decorative scenery in a jungle region.
